The TISSA Volleyball Moment

During the TISSA volleyball tournament, everyone already knew me as the “really bad” player. I wasn’t the strongest. I wasn’t the most skilled. And honestly, most teams didn’t expect much from me.

Even some of my own teammates were surprised when the ball came near me.

Then it happened.

The other team hit the ball over, and one of my teammates received it perfectly. He set the ball high into the air — but it was too close to the net, and I was the only one there.

Someone from the other team thought it was an easy mistake. He even started celebrating early, thinking the ball would just drop or that I would mess it up.

But I didn’t freeze.

I jumped.

Instead of panicking, I set the ball back over the net while I was still in the air. I didn’t just tap it — I angled my hands so it went straight down on their side.

No one expected it.

The ball dropped directly onto the court.

Point for us.

For a second, there was silence — then everyone exploded. People were screaming. My teammates were clapping so hard their mouths were almost falling open. Even the bench jumped up.

The guy who started celebrating froze. He couldn’t believe it.

And in that moment, I wasn’t the “bad player” anymore.

I was the one who surprised everyone.
